### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

common

### Is this a regression?

Yes

### Description

If you create a Project in angular 16 with
```bash
ng new angular-16-clean --routing --style=scss --prefix=app --standalone
```
Then add @angular/localize:
```bash
ng add @angular/localize
```
and then add cypress for e2e testing
```
ng add @cypress/schematic
```
A problem occurs where the configured Schematics in the `angular.json` (here an example):
```json
{
  "$schema": "./node_modules/@angular/cli/lib/config/schema.json",
  "version": 1,
  "newProjectRoot": "projects",
  "projects": {
    "angular-16-clean": {
      "projectType": "application",
      "schematics": {
        "@schematics/angular:component": {
          "style": "scss",
          "changeDetection": "OnPush",
          "viewEncapsulation": "None",
          "skipTests": false,
          "standalone": true,
          "prefix": "app"
        },
        "@schematics/angular:directive": {
          "prefix": "app",
          "standalone": true
        },
        "@schematics/angular:guard": {
          "functional": true,
          "implements": [
            "CanActivate"
          ]
        },
        "@schematics/angular:interceptor": {
          "functional": true
        },
        "@schematics/angular:library": {
          "prefix": "wl",
          "standalone": true
        },
        "@schematics/angular:pipe": {
          "standalone": true
        },
        "@schematics/angular:resolver": {
          "functional": true
        },
        "@schematics/angular:web-worker": {
          "snippet": true
        }
      },
      "root": "",
      "sourceRoot": "src",
      "prefix": "app",
      "architect": {
      }
    }
  }
}
```
If i now try to generate a component (or a other angular schematic) I encounter, that it doesn't apply the schematic to the command - it tries to use the default schematic - noticeable with compoennt, because they now throw an error because they don't find a module to get imported in:

```bash
% ng g c home
Could not find an NgModule. Use the '--skip-import' option to skip importing in NgModule.
```

I debbuged it and when i delete the following part in the angular.json it is working again:
```json
{
  "cli": {
    "schematicCollections": [
      "@cypress/schematic",
      "@schematics/angular"
    ]
  }
}
```
and I think it must be the `"@cypress/schematic"` part.

